29/09/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- Turkey would dispatch troops to Iraq because it is important that northern Iraq does not become a base for terrorists, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said Saturday (27 September). Gul was in the United States to attend the UN General Assembly and to meet with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan.
In other news, State Minister Kursad Tuzmen said Sunday that the UN has approved contracts for $102m his country had signed with Iraq before the war under the food-for-oil programme. He added that Turkish companies have been awarded contracts worth $200m for post-war Iraq. (Hurriyet, Milliyet, AFP - 28/09/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 27/09/03)
